article.headline: High Point 62, Elon 48
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 22 points to lead High Point to a 62-48 victory over Elon on Monday night. Reid connected on 9-of-16 attempts against the Phoenix (1-6). Troy Bowen finished with 11 points for High Point (5-3), and Jerald Minnis added 10. Brett James led the Phoenix with 15 points, and LeVonn Jordan had 11 points. But Elon also committed 26 turnovers. High Point took a 15-7 lead early and never gave it up, leading 28-19 at halftime. The Panthers outscored Elon 20-3 in the opening minutes of the second half, and Elon got no closer than the final 14-point deficit for the rest of the game.
